headline: Jacobs Secures Program Role in Pediatric Megaproject, Stock Up
summary: J lands a program manager role for a major Dallas pediatric hospital project with Children's Health and UT Southwestern.

headline: J Q2 Deep Dive: Backlog Expansion and Strategic Sector Growth Support Positive Outlook
summary: Global professional services company Jacobs Solutions (NYSE:J) missed Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q2 CY2025, but sales rose 5.1% year on year to $3.03 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $1.60 per share was 4.4% above analysts’ consensus estimates.

headline: The Top 5 Analyst Questions From Jacobs Solutions’s Q2 Earnings Call
summary: Jacobs Solutions’ second quarter results were well received by the market, as the company delivered higher non-GAAP earnings per share despite missing Wall Street’s revenue expectations. Management attributed the quarter’s performance to robust growth across advanced facilities and water sectors, as well as an expanding backlog fueled by strong demand in life sciences and data centers.
